cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: QUIC Protocol Implementation Evaluation Under Varying Bandwidth and File Size
  Conditions on Tartu and Tallinn Nodes
abstract: This dataset evaluates multiple QUIC protocol implementations under controlled
  bandwidth limits and file size configurations across two nodes. The experiment measures
  transfer performance, energy consumption, and file integrity through synchronized
  client-server workloads, capturing per-run metrics such as transfer duration, goodput,
  and checksum verification. Evaluation scripts aggregate results into statistical
  summaries and visualizations, comparing implementation behaviors under different
  constraints. Archive contents include compiled protocol binaries, per-run logs,
  and structured evaluation outputs for analysis.
